Dependency:
OS: Windows:
MinGW-w64 (https://www.mingw-w64.org/)
Make (installed in MinGW-w64)
CMake (https://cmake.org/download/)
  Third Parties:
    -- spdlog;


How to compile the project:
Install all submodules:
  git submodule update --init --recursive

Instruction 1:
Run the following script from the root dir:
./build.bat
In addition to, you can set as arguments threads count to make the project
./build.bat 12
where 12 - is count of threads used for project compilation

Instruction 2:
Compile project from the terminal:
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -G "MinGW Makefiles"
make

How to start up the project?
In case of building from the script (instruction 1) open the /app/ or /build/ folder and startup the binary with name app_tech_task_solution.exe
In case of building from the terminal (instruction 2) open the /build/ folder and startup the binary with name app_tech_task_solution.exe

How to change debug lvl?
-- Open the ThirdParty/spdlog/include/spdlog/common.h 
-- find SPDLOG_ACTIVE_LEVEL and set required lvl